Steps to install and compile chromium:

1. Linux Distribution:

64 bit Linux Precise 12.04.5, amd-64 distribution.

http://releases.ubuntu.com/12.04.5/

64-bit linux is essential!!!! Will not build properly without more
than 4GB of address space.

2. According to the google instructions, make sure you have at least 8 GB swap.

6. Get the google depot tools and add the path to the tools to my search paths

git clone https://chromium.googlesource.com/chromium/tools/depot_tools.git

Add 

export PATH=`pwd`/depot_tools:"$PATH"

to my .bashrc.

http://www.chromium.org/developers/how-tos/install-depot-tools

7. Get all the chrome dependencies using the instructions here:

https://code.google.com/p/chromium/wiki/LinuxBuildInstructionsPrerequisites

Using Sophiaâ€™s code copy, go to src/build and run the script
install_build_deps.sh

8. Configure the build using gyp

From src directory:

GYP_GENERATORS=ninja GYP_DEFINES="werror=" ./build/gyp_chromium

If you want to link with the dynamic libraries, use this:

GYP_GENERATORS=ninja GYP_DEFINES="werror=" ./build/gyp_chromium -D component=shared_library

Using dynamic libraries makes builds faster.


9. Build using ninja

for release:
ninja -C out/Release chrome

for debug 

ninja -C out/Debug chrome